        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>MEASURE RANGEAND DECLARE TARGET SQUARE:</strong>
            The range ruler may be used to
            determine the range between the throwing player and any possible target squares, before the
            target square is chosen and declared.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>TEST FOR QUALITY:</strong>
            The coach of the player performing the action rolls a D6
            to determine the quality of the throw.
        </p>
        <p>
            <strong>RESOLVE THROW:</strong>
            Where the thrown player lands, and how easily, depends upon
            the quality of the throw. If the throw is fumbled, the thrown player is dropped and will
            bounce.
        </p>
